Title: Parents and Children
Description: February 25
---
Oh, if only our parents were born at the same moment we were, how much
conflict and bitterness we would be spared. But parents and children
can only go after each otherâ€”not with each other. And so an abyss lies
between us, which, now and then, nothing but a little love can span.
